Create the PO Template (POT) file
=================================

For say indicatorfortune, open a terminal in indicatorfortune/src/indicatorfortune:

    xgettext --files-from=locale/POTFILES.in --output=locale/indicatorfortune.pot

Open indicatorfortune.pot in a text editor.
Edit the first three lines in the comment header as appropriate.
Set Project-Id-Version and Report-Msgid-Bugs-To appropriate values.
Ensure Content-Type contains charset=UTF-8 or use sed:

	sed -i -e 's/.*Content-Type.*/"Content-Type: text\/plain; charset=UTF-8\\n"/g' locale/indicatorfortune.pot


Create a PO file for each new translation
=========================================

http://www.gnu.org/software/gettext/manual/gettext.html#Creating

To create a Russian (ru) translation file,
open a terminal in indicatorfortune/src/indicatorfortune/locale:

    mkdir -p ru/LC_MESSAGES && \
    msginit --locale=ru --input=indicatorfortune.pot --output-file=ru/LC_MESSAGES/indicatorfortune.po --no-translator

Open locale/ru/LC_MESSAGES/indicatorfortune.po in a text editor and replace the first line in the header

	# SOME DESCRIPTIVE TITLE.

with

	# Russian translation for Indicator Fortune.

Replace the fourth line in the header

	# Automatically generated, ...

with

	# FIRST AUTHOR <EMAIL@ADDRESS>, YEAR.

replacing each tag as appropriate.

Replace 

	"Last-Translator: Automatically generated\n"

with translator name and email address.

Replace

	"Language-Team: none\n"

with team name (typically the name of the language in English).

For each msgid, replace with the appropriate translated text.


Updating POT and PO files
=========================

If text has been added/edited/removed, create a new POT file as above.

For a translator to update an existing PO file,
take the newly generated POT file and
open a terminal in indicatorfortune/src/indicatorfortune/locale:

    msgmerge ru/LC_MESSAGES/indicatorfortune.po indicatorfortune.pot -o ru/LC_MESSAGES/indicatorfortune.po

Which replaces the existing indicatorfortune.po with a new/merged version.

Translations for the strings which haven't changed are copied across.
Translations which have slightly changed are mark with the tag "fuzzy".
Update "fuzzy" translations as appropriate.
Update the header as appropriate.